zi atrocities witnessed by Selvinsky, and shows that in 1943, as Stalin's regime increasingly refused to report the annihilation of Jews in the occupied territories, Selvinsky paid a high price for his writings and actions. This book features over 60 rare photographs and illustrations and includes translations of Selvinsky's principal Shoah poems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)vPoetry. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zSoviet Union. 0aPoets, Russiany20th centuryvBiography. 70(DE-601)1041625970(DE-588)4006020-2aBesetzung2gnd 70(DE-601)1046825900(DE-588)4073091-8aJudenvernichtung2gnd 70(DE-601)1061533900(DE-588)4056883-0aStalinismus2gnd 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015z978311068814640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618111913423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618111913.jpg  a978-3-11-068814-6  ASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015c2008d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG